{"type":"message","id":"f2def4ad","parentId":"39e9191f","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:48:39.889Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"用户问为什么网络不能用。我需要解释一下当前的情况。根据之前的尝试，web_search 返回了 \"fetch failed\" 错误，web_fetch 虽然能访问但返回的内容有限。\n\n可能的原因：\n1. 网络配置问题\n2. API 密钥问题（Brave Search API）\n3. 防火墙或代理问题\n4. 临时网络故障\n\n我应该向用户解释情况，并继续完成文档创建的任务，使用我已经掌握的 feishu-create-doc 技能来实际操作，而不是依赖网络搜索。\n\n让我用正确的方式调用 feishu_create_doc 工具。根据之前读取的 SKILL.md，这个工具是通过 MCP 调用的，但在 OpenClaw 中，我应该直接使用工具调用的方式。\n\n让我尝试使用 sessions_spawn 或者其他方式来调用这个工具。实际上，在 OpenClaw 中，MCP 工具应该是可以直接通过 agent 调用的。让我重新尝试使用正确的方式。\n\n其实我应该直接使用 MCP 工具调用。在 OpenClaw 中，当插件注册后，工具应该可以直接使用。让我尝试用更直接的方式。\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"网络搜索暂时不可用可能是以下原因：\n\n1. **Brave Search API 配置问题** - 可能需要 API 密钥或配额限制\n2. **临时网络故障** - 网关到外网的连接可能有波动\n3. **防火墙/代理限制** - 某些网络环境可能限制外部访问\n\n不过这不影响我们使用飞书文档功能。我已经有完整的 `feishu-create-doc` 技能说明，可以直接为你演示创建飞书文档。\n\n让我直接用正确的方式调用工具来创建文档：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_88a5f60b433e49a5b5ae0a7c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace-fox-feishu && openclaw agent --help 2>&1 | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"custom-dashscope-aliyuncs-com","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":6,"output":394,"cacheRead":11138,"cacheWrite":10204,"totalTokens":21742,"cost":{"input":6.6e-7,"output":0.00011032,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00011098}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774000111044}}
{"type":"message","id":"d225c720","parentId":"f2def4ad","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:48:41.907Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_88a5f60b433e49a5b5ae0a7c","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.13 (61d171a) — I've seen your commit messages. We'll work on that together.\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line|feishu|openclaw-lark|nostr|msteams|mattermost|nextcloud-talk|matrix|bluebubbles|zalo|zalouser|synology-chat|tlon\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n                             | xhigh\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)"}],"details":{"status":